(40, 11, 25, 46, 2, 6, 8, 'hid these things from the wise', 'Hidden Wisdom Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''hidden wisdom'' revealed to the humble. Matthew highlights that God reveals truths to ''babes,'' while 1 Corinthians speaks of ''hidden wisdom'' ordained by God.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 26, 55, 1, 9, 9, 'for so it seemed good in thy sight', 'Divine Purpose and Grace', 'Both passages emphasize the divine purpose behind God''s actions. Matthew 11:26 speaks of what seemed good in God''s sight, while 2 Timothy 1:9 highlights God''s purpose and grace given before the world began.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 26, 18, 33, 13, 13, 'for so it seemed good in thy sight', 'Divine Will and Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of divine authority and the inscrutability of God''s decisions. Matthew 11:26 reflects acceptance of God''s will, while Job 33:13 questions human resistance to God''s unaccountable actions.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 26, 23, 46, 10, 10, 'for so it seemed good in thy sight', 'Divine Counsel and Pleasure', 'Both passages emphasize the sovereignty of God in His decisions. Matthew reflects on God''s pleasure in His actions, while Isaiah declares that God''s counsel will stand and fulfill His desires.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 26, 42, 10, 21, 21, NULL, 'Connection of Divine Approval', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''even so, Father; for so it seemed good in thy sight,'' highlighting a shared theme of divine approval in God''s revelation. This connection underscores the idea that God''s choices align with His wisdom and purpose.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 26, 45, 9, 18, 18, 'for so it seemed good in thy sight', 'Divine Sovereignty and Mercy', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s sovereign choice in dispensing mercy and judgment. Both passages emphasize that God''s decisions are ultimately based on His will and what seems good in His sight.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 26, 45, 11, 33, 36, 'for so it seemed good in thy sight', 'God''s Wisdom and Good Pleasure', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s wisdom and the goodness of His decisions. Both passages reflect on the unsearchable nature of God''s judgments and the idea that His actions are ultimately for His good pleasure.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 26, 49, 1, 9, 9, 'for so it seemed good in thy sight', 'Good Pleasure of God', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of God''s good pleasure in His actions. Matthew 11:26 states it seemed good in God''s sight, while Ephesians 1:9 mentions His good pleasure in revealing His will.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 27, 40, 28, 18, 18, 'All things are delivered unto me of my Father', 'Authority of the Son', 'Both passages emphasize the authority given to the Son. In Matthew 11:27, it is stated that all things are delivered to the Son by the Father, while Matthew 28:18 declares that all power is given to Him in heaven and earth.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 27, 43, 14, 6, 9, NULL, 'Knowledge of the Father', 'Both passages emphasize the unique relationship between the Father and the Son. Matthew highlights that no man knows the Father except the Son, while John states that knowing the Son equates to knowing the Father.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 27, 42, 10, 22, 22, 'All things are delivered unto me of my Father', 'Connection of Divine Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize the unique relationship between the Father and the Son, highlighting that knowledge of each is revealed through the other. The phrasing regarding all things being delivered and the knowledge of the Son and Father is nearly identical, reinforcing their interconnectedness.', 'parallel', 0.937, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 27, 63, 1, 9, 9, NULL, 'Knowledge of the Father and Son', 'This connection highlights the relationship between knowing the Father and the Son. Both passages emphasize that knowledge of God is contingent upon the revelation of the Son.', 'theme', 0.8319999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 27, 43, 17, 25, 26, NULL, 'Knowledge of the Father and Son', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowledge between the Father and the Son. Both passages emphasize that the Son knows the Father and reveals Him to others, indicating a unique relationship of understanding and revelation.', 'theme', 0.7969999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 27, 62, 2, 23, 23, NULL, 'Connection of Father and Son', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the Father and the Son. Matthew 11:27 states that no one knows the Father except the Son, while 1 John 2:23 asserts that denying the Son means one does not have the Father.', 'theme', 0.776, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 27, 62, 5, 19, 20, NULL, 'Knowledge of the Father and Son', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowing God through the Son. Both passages emphasize that understanding of the Father comes through the Son, as seen in Matthew 11:27 and reiterated in 1 John 5:20.', 'theme', 0.72, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 28, 23, 55, 1, 3, 'come unto me', 'Invitation to Come and Rest', 'Both passages emphasize an invitation to come to God for sustenance and rest. Matthew 11:28''s call to ''come unto me'' parallels Isaiah 55:1''s invitation to ''come ye to the waters,'' highlighting a shared theme of divine provision for the weary and thirsty.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 28, 40, 11, 29, 29, 'I will give you rest', 'Connection of Rest and Yoke', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of finding rest. The invitation to come for rest in the first verse leads directly to the call to take on the yoke in the second, suggesting a relationship between rest and learning from Jesus.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 28, 43, 6, 37, 37, NULL, 'Invitation to Come', 'Both passages emphasize the invitation to come to Jesus for rest and acceptance. Matthew highlights the call to those who labor, while John assures that all who come will not be cast out.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 28, 43, 7, 37, 37, 'Come unto me', 'Invitation to Come and Receive', 'Both passages emphasize an invitation to come to Jesus for relief and satisfaction. Matthew speaks of rest for the weary, while John offers drink for the thirsty, highlighting a common theme of seeking fulfillment in Christ.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 28, 48, 5, 1, 1, 'heavy laden', 'Rest and Freedom in Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of liberation from burdens. Both passages emphasize the relief from labor and bondage through Christ''s invitation and freedom.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 28, 66, 22, 17, 17, 'Come unto me', 'Invitation to Come and Rest', 'Both passages emphasize an invitation to come to Jesus for relief and sustenance. Matthew speaks of rest for the weary, while Revelation invites the thirsty to take the water of life freely.', 'theme', 0.895, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 28, 23, 48, 17, 18, 'I will give you rest', 'Rest and Peace Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of rest and peace found in both passages. Matthew 11:28 invites the weary to find rest, while Isaiah 48:18 speaks of peace flowing like a river for those who heed God''s commandments.', 'theme', 0.853, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 29, 24, 6, 16, 16, NULL, 'Rest for Your Souls', 'Both passages emphasize finding rest for the soul. Matthew invites followers to take on Jesus'' yoke, while Jeremiah encourages seeking the old paths for rest. This connection highlights a shared theme of spiritual rest.', 'theme', 0.748, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 29, 62, 2, 6, 6, 'meek and lowly in heart', 'Walking in Meekness and Humility', 'This connection highlights the call to emulate Christ''s character. Both passages emphasize the importance of walking in a manner reflective of Jesus'' meekness and lowliness.', 'theme', 0.5589999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 29, 50, 2, 7, 8, 'meek and lowly in heart', 'Meekness and Humility Connection', 'This connection highlights the themes of meekness and humility in both passages. Matthew emphasizes Jesus'' meekness and lowliness, while Philippians describes His humility and obedience.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 29, 43, 13, 15, 15, 'meek and lowly in heart', 'Meekness and Example', 'This connection highlights the theme of humility and service. Both passages emphasize the importance of learning from Jesus'' example of meekness and applying it in our actions towards others.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 29, 42, 6, 46, 48, 'learn of me', 'Connection of Obedience and Rest', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of following Jesus'' teachings. In Matthew, the call to take His yoke suggests learning from Him, while in Luke, obedience to His sayings is highlighted as foundational for stability.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 29, 40, 7, 24, 24, 'learn of me', 'Wisdom and Rest Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of following Jesus'' teachings. In Matthew 11:29, learning from Jesus leads to rest, while Matthew 7:24 highlights the wisdom of acting on His words, suggesting that true rest comes from obedience.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 29, 43, 15, 10, 14, 'find rest unto your souls', 'Connection of Love and Rest', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of love and obedience. In Matthew, finding rest is linked to learning from Jesus, who embodies meekness, while John highlights that abiding in love comes from keeping commandments, particularly to love one another.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
